org.kramerlab.coffer.api

Interface ModelService


  • @Path(value="")
public interface ModelService
    Java API and REST API Interface for "COFFER - Collision-free Filtered Circular Fingerprint-based QSARs" ("http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de")
    REST methods are documented below.
    Author:
    Martin GÃ¼tlein guetlein@uni-mainz.de

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      InputStream depict(String smiles, String size)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/depict
      content-type: image/png
      params:
      smiles: compound smiles string
      size: integer to specify width and height (optional), otherwise depends on compound with default bond size
      returns: image
      InputStream depictActiveIcon(String probability, String drawHelp) 
      InputStream depictAppDomain(String modelId, String smiles) 
      InputStream depictMatch(String smiles, String size, String atoms, String highlightOutgoingBonds, String activating, String crop)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/depictMatch
      content-type: image/png
      params:
      smiles: compound smiles string
      size: integer to specify width and height (optional), otherwise depends on compound with default bond size
      atoms: comma separated atom indices to be highlighted
      highlightOutgoingBonds: true (optional) if outgoing bonds of fragment should be highlighted
      activating: true/false (optional) if match should be colored as activating/de-activating instead of neutral
      crop: true (optional) if image should be cropped around matching atoms
      returns: image
      InputStream depictMultiMatch(String smiles, String size, String model)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/depictMultiMatch
      content-type: image/png
      params:
      smiles: compound smiles string
      size: integer to specify width and height (optional), otherwise depends on compound with default bond size
      model: id of the model that is used to predict the compound
      returns: image
      String getAppDomain(String modelId, String smiles, String size) 
      Compound getCompound(String compoundId)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/compound/compoundId
      content-type: text/html, application/json, chemical/x-daylight-smiles
      returns: compound
      String getCompoundInfo(String service, String smiles)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/info/service/smiles
      content-type: text/html
      returns: compound info fetched from another service
      String getDocumentation()
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/doc
      content-type: text/html
      returns: documentation
      Fragment getFragment(String modelId, String fragmentId, String size, String smiles)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/modelId/fragment/fragmentId
      content-type: application/json, text/html
      params:
      size: integer specifying the number of fragments shown (default: 10)
      smiles: a compound that the fragment is matched on (optional)
      returns: fragment
      Model getModel(String modelId)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/modelId
      content-type: application/json, text/html
      returns: model
      Model[] getModels()
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/
      content-type: application/json, text/html, "text/uri-list"
      returns: list of models
      Prediction getPrediction(String modelId, String predictionId, String hideFragments, String size)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/modelId/prediction/predictionId
      content-type: application/json, text/html
      params:
      hideFragments: filter options for fragments: "hideSuperFragments"|"hideSubFragments"|"hideNoFragments"
      size: integer specifying the number of fragments shown (default: 10)
      returns: single-model prediction
      Prediction[] getPredictions(String predictionId, String wait)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/prediction/predictionId
      content-type: application/json, text/html, "text/uri-list"
      params:
      wait: integer encoding the number of expected results
      returns: list of single-model predictions, empty predictions trailing if num predictions is < wait
      InputStream getValidationChart(String modelId)
      request: GET "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/modelId/validation
      content-type: image/png
      returns: image
      javax.ws.rs.core.Response predict(String compound)
      request: POST "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/
      params:
      "compoundSmiles": SMILES String
      returns: redirect to prediction with all models
      javax.ws.rs.core.Response predict(String modelId, String compound, String compoundURI)
      request: POST "http://coffer.informatik.uni-mainz.de"/modelId
      params:
      "compoundSmiles": SMILES String
      returns: redirect to single-model prediction
      javax.ws.rs.core.Response predictAppDomain(String modelId, String compound)
